<TITLE> Faridpur road crash kills 17 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Faridpur, Jan 1 (bdnews24.com)  At least 17 people, including three women and three children, were killed when a bus fell into a roadside ditch at Diknagar in Kanaipur Union on the Dhaka-Khulna highway early on Friday. Fourteen of them were killed on the spot while the others died on their way to hospital, Noore Alam Siddiqee, officer-in-charge of Kotwali Police Station, told bdnews24.com. Some 56 people were injured in the accident. The injured were rushed to the Faridpur Medical College Hospital. None could be identified immediately after the fatal accident. The Dhaka-bound Shoukhin Paribahan lost control and slipped into the ditch at around 1am, Siddiqee said. Police and fire fighters with the help of local people were engaged in rescue operation just after the accident took place, Siddiqee said. Faridpur district administration has announced a grant of Tk 4,000 and 1,000 for each family of the deceased and injured respectively, officials said. bdnews2
